{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4c250d5-8ad1-43c8-92ef-42936c5be2c0","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .dmp file, though none of my specialized skills cover dump **analysis** (only collection).\n\nHere's how to analyze it:\n\n**Recommended tool: `dotnet-dump analyze`**\n\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your.dmp\n```\n\n**Key commands inside the analyzer:**\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview (for OOM crashes) |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a specific thread |\n\n**Typical workflow:**\n1. Run `pe` to check for an unhandled exception\n2. Run `clrthreads` to find faulting thread\n3. `setthread` + `clrstack` to inspect its stack\n\n---\n\nIf you can share the dump file in this environment or tell me more (exception type, symptoms), I can help you run the commands and interpret the output. Is `dotnet-dump` available on your system, or would you like me to check/install it here?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc934cf9-07c8-497e-a059-dce78c7f8478","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any of them are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files\n\n\nNone of the available skills can help with dump analysis, but I can guide the user toward the right tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`, WinDbg, or lldb depending on their platform. I should ask if the dump file is accessible and offer to help walk through the analysis process if they have access to these tools.","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"C3C6:27C37:1DE682F:218CC6F:6A07C3EC"},"id":"225e23e1-f3a2-4c3d-bae6-e544dea9c451","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:10:18.625Z","parentId":"96988fea-5a59-4b16-b248-01180aaf2063"}
